summary.p:
i. providing a sample wherein target nucleic acids are present in a low amount;
ii. generating a reduced representation library of said target nucleic acids, using the steps of
fragmenting said target nucleic acids;
ligating adaptors to said fragments;
selecting a subset of said adaptor-ligated fragments;
simultaneously with or after selecting a subset, amplifying said subset;
iii. massively parallel sequencing said reduced representation library; and
iv. identifying variants in said target nucleic acids by analyzing results obtained by said sequencing.

1. In case of cell preparation, said cell preparation preferably comprising;
a. Isolating at least one cell(s), preferably a single or a few cells, e.g. from in vitro or in vivo generated pre-implantation embryos
b. Lysing the cells
